<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=1950&amp;p=10786#p10786"><![CDATA[
OK. I added blue highlights option.<br />I had tried green, to escape from MS brainwashing blue <img src="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/images/smilies/icon_lol.gif" alt=":lol:" title="Laughing" /> <br />Put option for a matching black submenu.<br />Also an option for more of those dirty ugly dark clouds.<br />I may have gone too far on this option. <br /><br />I have yet to fully explore and understand menu transparencies,<br />so I will skip for now. <br />If there was a way to fuzzy up the Win8 desktop, I would love to add it.<br /><br />If you want to try. Use Resource Hacker to save a main bitmap, from the skin file. <br />Use Pixelformer to modify the alpha layer of that file. Put back in skin file.<br />Change the main opacity text in file to one of the six transparency types.<br />Good luck. <img src="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/images/smilies/icon_e_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" /><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=856">juniper7</a> — Sat Feb 08, 2014 7:22 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
